    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Keep Pressing Iran Over Trial of Jews</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rosalind F Maringer letter deplores Iran's conviction of 10 Jews on charge of spying for Israel (July 2 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''10 Jews Convicted by Iranian Court in Espionage Case'' (front page, July 2):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''10 Jews Convicted by Iranian Court in Espionage Case'' (front page, July 2):</p>
        <p>As a Jew who was the secretary to the Iranian ambassador to the United Nations during a period when the shah reigned, I am deeply distressed by Iran's conviction of 10 Jews in Shiraz. World opinion held the shah in low esteem for many reasons, but religious intolerance or persecution was not one of them.</p>
        <p>The trial of these men was a travesty, and world opinion must rally against a government whose ultimate intent is to obliterate religious freedom. To be sure, this trial is only the beginning. Our fear should be that other governments made up of religious militants of any persuasion will follow suit, and Jews will surely not be the only victims.</p>
        <p>Has the world learned nothing from history?</p>
        <p>ROSALIND F. MARINGER  Greenwich, Conn., July 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
